  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Providing safe and equitable access to quality and inclusive education in a protective environment for children affected by the conflict in North Eastern Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This is a 12 month project for implementing education in emergencies activities in northeast Nigeria. The project will create access to education for conflict affected children, improve the quality of learning while providing a protective learning environment for children under the do no harm policy. 
To achieve the above project objectives, Plan international will re-establish temporary learning spaces, conduct awareness raising, community mobilisation and other activities to create access while to achieve improved quality, the action will train teachers, provide teacher materials, and in-service and mentorship sessions. The action will also train School Based Management Committees, train learners on life skills, establish and clearly mark gender segregated latrines, incorporate safe schools approach and other interventions in a bid to provide a protective learning environment. 
The proposed action will target children aged 3-6 both boys and girls to benefit from early childhood development (ECD) and children aged 6-17 to benefit from basic education. Both in and out of school children will be targeted through the project with an aim of increasing enrollment, retention as well as increasing school attendance. 
The project will target both host, returnee and IDP communities in the 3 target local government areas of Konduga and Gwoza in Borno state and Madagali in Adamawa state.</narrative>
  </description>
